---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="What I Use — Yannik Peschke" 
  description="Tools, frameworks, and technologies I use for software development."
>

<h1>What I Use</h1>
<p class="page-intro">
  The tools, frameworks, and technologies I use for software development. This list reflects my current 
  preferences and the stack I'm most productive with.
</p>

<section class="category-section">
  <h2>Languages &amp; Tools</h2>
  <div class="simple-list">
    <div class="simple-list-item">
      <strong>Classic Frontend</strong>
      <p class="category-intro">
        Yes, I learned frontend when jQuery was the GOAT! Having a solid foundation on classic technology
        without abstraction layers is mandatory to actually understand any advanced framework or toolkit
        (looking at you React and Tailwind).
      </p>
      <div class="stack-tags">
        <span class="stack-tag">HTML5</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Handlebars</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">CSS3</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Sass</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">JavaScript</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">jQuery</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">NodeJs</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="simple-list-item">
      <strong>Modern Frontend</strong>
      <p class="category-intro">
        Advanced tools I work with for modern web application development with a focus on first level citizen
        products for micro frontend architectures.
      </p>
      <div class="stack-tags">
        <span class="stack-tag">TypeScript</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">React</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">ModernJs</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Rsbuild</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Rslib</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Rspress</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Playwright</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Vitest</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">ModuleFederation</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Nx</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="simple-list-item">
      <strong>Bundler</strong>
      <p class="category-intro">
        It is my daily business to adapt, maintain and modernize/migrate bundlers to keep pipeline performance,
        frontend infrastructure and developer experience on a peak level. This also includes writing custom
        Rspack plugins (Rust bundler following the amazing API architecture philosophy of Webpack).
      </p>
      <div class="stack-tags">
        <span class="stack-tag">Rspack</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Webpack</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Gulp</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Bower</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Grunt</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="simple-list-item">
      <strong>Infra</strong>
      <p class="category-intro">
        I am not a DevOps specialist but I am familiar configuring my own docker-compose files, gitlab pipelines
        and reverse-proxy rules on my own.
      </p>
      <div class="stack-tags">
        <span class="stack-tag">Gitlab</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Docker</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Kubernetes</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Traefik</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="simple-list-item">
      <strong>Generic</strong>
      <p class="category-intro">
        Additional tech I like to use to keep the work rolling.
      </p>
      <div class="stack-tags">
        <span class="stack-tag">OAuth</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">OpenApi</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Lua</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Neovim</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">SonarQube</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Bash</span>
        <span class="stack-tag">Git</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="category-section">
  <h2>My Dev Setup</h2>
  <p class="category-intro category-intro-standalone">
    I'm a strong believer in a highly customized and efficient development environment. My setup is built around a few key tools that help me stay productive and focused.
  </p>
  <div class="simple-list">
    <div class="simple-list-item">
      <strong>Operating System</strong>
      <p class="category-intro">
        My go-to setup is Arch Linux paired with Hyprland, a dynamic tiling Wayland compositor, to manage my windows and workspaces with ease. Unfortunately, I am bound to a Windows machine at work trying my best to be friends with WSL 🙈
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="simple-list-item">
      <strong>Neovim</strong>
      <p class="category-intro">
        My custom-built Neovim configuration is the heart of my coding workflow. It's a lightweight, powerful, and keyboard-centric editor tailored to my needs.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="simple-list-item">
      <strong>Tmux</strong>
      <p class="category-intro">
        I use Tmux to manage multiple terminal sessions and windows from a single screen. This lets me handle different tasks—from running tests to monitoring logs—without ever leaving my terminal.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="simple-list-item">
      <strong>Lazygit & LazyDocker</strong>
      <p class="category-intro">
        To interact with Git and Docker in a fast and intuitive way, I rely on these two tools. They provide a simple, terminal-based user interface that makes complex tasks quick and effortless.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="dev-setup-outro">
    My entire setup is designed to be fast, keyboard-driven, and distraction-free, allowing me to fully immerse myself in the code.
  </p>
</section>

</Layout>

<style>
.page-intro {
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
}

.category-section {
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
}

.tools-grid {
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--spacing-md);
}

.tool-item {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
  gap: var(--spacing-md);
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
  padding-left: var(--spacing-lg);
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  background: transparent;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
  position: relative;
}

.tool-item:hover {
  border-left-color: var(--accent);
  padding-left: calc(var(--spacing-lg) + 10px);
}

.tool-item:last-child {
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}

.tool-item:last-child:hover {
  border-left-color: var(--accent);
}

.tool-name {
  font-family: var(--font-main);
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--accent);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}

.tool-name::before {
  content: ">";
  margin-right: 10px;
  color: var(--accent);
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateX(-10px);
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
}

.tool-item:hover .tool-name::before {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateX(0);
}

.tool-description {
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.simple-list {
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--spacing-sm);
}

.simple-list-item {
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
  padding-left: var(--spacing-lg);
  background-color: transparent;
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  font-size: 1rem;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
  position: relative;
}

.simple-list-item:hover {
  border-left-color: var(--accent);
  padding-left: calc(var(--spacing-lg) + 10px);
}

.simple-list-item strong {
  font-family: var(--font-main);
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--text-primary);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  display: block;
  position: relative;
}

.simple-list-item strong::before {
  content: ">";
  position: absolute;
  left: -16px;
  top: 0;
  color: var(--accent);
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateX(-10px);
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
}

.simple-list-item:hover strong::before {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateX(0);
}

.simple-list-item:hover strong {
  color: var(--accent);
}

.simple-list-item span {
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}

.category-section h2 {
  margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
}

.category-section h2:first-child {
  margin-top: 0;
}

.category-intro {
  margin: var(--spacing-xs) 0 var(--spacing-sm);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}

.category-intro-standalone {
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
}

.dev-setup-outro {
  margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}

.stack-tags {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: var(--spacing-xs);
}

.stack-tag {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
  border-radius: 999px;
  border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  background-color: transparent;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
}

.simple-list-item:hover .stack-tag {
  border-color: var(--accent);
  color: var(--accent);
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .tool-item {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--spacing-xs);
  }
}
</style>
